      "title": "Variables",
      "intro": {
        "title": "Storing values",
        "bodyMarkdown": "In Python you assign a name to a value with `=`. Names are often called **variables**.\n\n```python\nscore = 10\nname = \"Asha\"\nis_active = True\n```\n\nVariables can hold numbers, text, booleans, and more. You can reassign them as your program runs.\n\n```python\nscore = score + 5\nname = \"Asha K\"\n```\n\nUse descriptive snake_case names like `user_age` and `total_price`.",
        "readMore": {
          "label": "Read more (Python docs)",
          "url": "https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/introduction.html#first-steps-towards-programming",
          "source": "Python Software Foundation — Python 3 Tutorial"
        }
      },
